{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":0,"text":"So, indeed, I have spent my life"},{"time":2000,"text":"looking into the lives of presidents who are no longer alive."},{"time":6000,"text":"Waking up with Abraham Lincoln in the morning,"},{"time":8000,"text":"thinking of Franklin Roosevelt when I went to bed at night."},{"time":11000,"text":"But when I try and think about what I've learned"},{"time":13000,"text":"about the meaning in life, my mind keeps wandering back"},{"time":16000,"text":"to a seminar that I took when I was a graduate student at Harvard"},{"time":19000,"text":"with the great psychologist Erik Erikson."}]},{"cues":[{"time":22000,"text":"He taught us that the richest and fullest lives"},{"time":25000,"text":"attempt to achieve an inner balance between three realms:"},{"time":29000,"text":"work, love and play."},{"time":32000,"text":"And that to pursue one realm to the disregard of the other,"},{"time":34000,"text":"is to open oneself to ultimate sadness in older age."},{"time":38000,"text":"Whereas to pursue all three with equal dedication,"},{"time":40000,"text":"is to make possible a life filled not only with achievement,"},{"time":43000,"text":"but with serenity."}]},{"cues":[{"time":45000,"text":"So since I tell stories, let me look back"},{"time":47000,"text":"on the lives of two of the presidents I've studied to illustrate this point --"},{"time":51000,"text":"Abraham Lincoln and Lyndon Johnson."},{"time":54000,"text":"As for that first sphere of work,"},{"time":56000,"text":"I think what Abraham Lincoln's life suggests"},{"time":59000,"text":"is that fierce ambition is a good thing."},{"time":62000,"text":"He had a huge ambition."},{"time":64000,"text":"But it wasn't simply for office or power or celebrity or fame --"},{"time":68000,"text":"what it was for was to accomplish something worthy enough in life"},{"time":72000,"text":"so that he could make the world a little better place for his having lived in it."}]},{"cues":[{"time":77000,"text":"Even as a child, it seemed, Lincoln dreamed heroic dreams."},{"time":81000,"text":"He somehow had to escape that hard-scrabble farm"},{"time":84000,"text":"from which he was born."},{"time":85000,"text":"No schooling was possible for him,"},{"time":87000,"text":"except a few weeks here, a few weeks there."},{"time":89000,"text":"But he read books in every spare moment he could find."},{"time":92000,"text":"It was said when he got a copy of the King James Bible"},{"time":94000,"text":"or \"Aesop's Fables,\" he was so excited he couldn't sleep."},{"time":97000,"text":"He couldn't eat."},{"time":98000,"text":"The great poet Emily Dickinson once said,"},{"time":100000,"text":"\"There is no frigate like a book to take us lands away.\""},{"time":104000,"text":"How true for Lincoln."}]},{"cues":[{"time":105000,"text":"Though he never would travel to Europe,"},{"time":107000,"text":"he went with Shakespeare's kings to merry England,"},{"time":109000,"text":"he went with Lord Byron's poetry to Spain and Portugal."},{"time":112000,"text":"Literature allowed him to transcend his surroundings."},{"time":116000,"text":"But there were so many losses in his early life"},{"time":118000,"text":"that he was haunted by death."},{"time":120000,"text":"His mother died when he was only nine years old;"},{"time":122000,"text":"his only sister, Sarah, in childbirth a few years later;"},{"time":126000,"text":"and his first love, Ann Rutledge, at the age of 22."},{"time":129000,"text":"Moreover, when his mother lay dying,"},{"time":131000,"text":"she did not hold out for him the hope"},{"time":133000,"text":"that they would meet in an afterworld."},{"time":135000,"text":"She simply said to him,"},{"time":136000,"text":"\"Abraham, I'm going away from you now, and I shall never return.\""},{"time":140000,"text":"As a result he became obsessed with the thought"},{"time":142000,"text":"that when we die our life is swept away -- dust to dust."}]},{"cues":[{"time":145000,"text":"But only as he grew older did he develop"},{"time":148000,"text":"a certain consolation from an ancient Greek notion --"},{"time":150000,"text":"but followed by other cultures as well --"},{"time":153000,"text":"that if you could accomplish something worthy in your life,"},{"time":155000,"text":"you could live on in the memory of others."},{"time":158000,"text":"Your honor and your reputation would outlive your earthly existence."},{"time":163000,"text":"And that worthy ambition became his lodestar."},{"time":165000,"text":"It carried him through the one significant depression that he suffered"},{"time":169000,"text":"when he was in his early 30s."}]},{"cues":[{"time":171000,"text":"Three things had combined to lay him low."},{"time":173000,"text":"He had broken his engagement with Mary Todd,"},{"time":175000,"text":"not certain he was ready to marry her,"},{"time":177000,"text":"but knowing how devastating it was to her that he did that."},{"time":180000,"text":"His one intimate friend, Joshua Speed, was leaving Illinois"},{"time":183000,"text":"to go back to Kentucky because Speed's father had died."},{"time":186000,"text":"And his political career in the state legislature"},{"time":188000,"text":"was on a downward slide."},{"time":190000,"text":"He was so depressed that friends worried he was suicidal."},{"time":193000,"text":"They took all knives and razors and scissors from his room."},{"time":196000,"text":"And his great friend Speed went to his side and said,"},{"time":199000,"text":"\"Lincoln, you must rally or you will die.\""},{"time":201000,"text":"He said that, \"I would just as soon die right now,"},{"time":204000,"text":"but I've not yet done anything to make any human being"},{"time":207000,"text":"remember that I have lived.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":209000,"text":"So fueled by that ambition, he returned to the state legislature."},{"time":213000,"text":"He eventually won a seat in Congress."},{"time":216000,"text":"He then ran twice for the Senate, lost twice."},{"time":219000,"text":"\"Everyone is broken by life,\" Ernest Hemingway once said,"},{"time":221000,"text":"\"but some people are stronger in the broken places.\""},{"time":224000,"text":"So then he surprised the nation with an upset victory"},{"time":227000,"text":"for the presidency over three far more experienced,"},{"time":230000,"text":"far more educated, far more celebrated rivals."},{"time":234000,"text":"And then when he won the general election,"},{"time":236000,"text":"he stunned the nation even more"},{"time":238000,"text":"by appointing each of these three rivals into his Cabinet."},{"time":241000,"text":"It was an unprecedented act at the time because everybody thought,"},{"time":244000,"text":"\"He'll look like a figurehead compared to these people.\""},{"time":247000,"text":"They said, \"Why are you doing this, Lincoln?\""},{"time":249000,"text":"He said, \"Look, these are the strongest"},{"time":251000,"text":"and most able men in the country."},{"time":253000,"text":"The country is in peril. I need them by my side.\""},{"time":256000,"text":"But perhaps my old friend Lyndon Johnson"},{"time":258000,"text":"might have put it in less noble fashion:"},{"time":260000,"text":"\"Better to have your enemies inside the tent pissing out,"},{"time":263000,"text":"than outside the tent pissing in.\""},{"time":265000,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":267000,"text":"But it soon became clear that Abraham Lincoln"},{"time":270000,"text":"would emerge as the undisputed captain of this unruly team."},{"time":274000,"text":"For each of them soon came to understand"},{"time":277000,"text":"that he possessed an unparalleled array of"},{"time":279000,"text":"emotional strengths and political skills"},{"time":281000,"text":"that proved far more important than the thinness of his external résumé."},{"time":285000,"text":"For one thing, he possessed an uncanny ability"},{"time":287000,"text":"to empathize with and to think about other peoples' point of view."},{"time":291000,"text":"He repaired injured feelings that might have escalated"},{"time":293000,"text":"into permanent hostility."},{"time":295000,"text":"He shared credit with ease,"},{"time":297000,"text":"assumed responsibility for the failure of his subordinates,"},{"time":300000,"text":"constantly acknowledged his errors and learned from his mistakes."},{"time":304000,"text":"These are the qualities we should be looking for in our candidates in 2008."},{"time":307000,"text":"(Applause)"},{"time":310000,"text":"He refused to be provoked by petty grievances."},{"time":314000,"text":"He never submitted to jealousy or brooded over perceived slights."},{"time":318000,"text":"And he expressed his unshakeable convictions"},{"time":320000,"text":"in everyday language, in metaphors, in stories."},{"time":324000,"text":"And with a beauty of language -- almost as if"},{"time":326000,"text":"the Shakespeare and the poetry he had so loved as a child"},{"time":328000,"text":"had worked their way into his very soul."}]},{"cues":[{"time":332000,"text":"In 1863, when the Emancipation Proclamation was signed,"},{"time":335000,"text":"he brought his old friend, Joshua Speed, back to the White House,"},{"time":337000,"text":"and remembered that conversation of decades before, when he was so sad."},{"time":341000,"text":"And he, pointing to the Proclamation, said,"},{"time":343000,"text":"\"I believe, in this measure, my fondest hopes will be realized.\""},{"time":348000,"text":"But as he was about to put his signature on the Proclamation"},{"time":351000,"text":"his own hand was numb and shaking"},{"time":353000,"text":"because he had shaken a thousand hands that morning at a New Year's reception."},{"time":356000,"text":"So he put the pen down."},{"time":358000,"text":"He said, \"If ever my soul were in an act, it is in this act."},{"time":361000,"text":"But if I sign with a shaking hand,"},{"time":363000,"text":"posterity will say, 'He hesitated.'\""},{"time":365000,"text":"So he waited until he could take up the pen"},{"time":367000,"text":"and sign with a bold and clear hand."},{"time":370000,"text":"But even in his wildest dreams,"},{"time":372000,"text":"Lincoln could never have imagined"},{"time":373000,"text":"how far his reputation would reach."}]},{"cues":[{"time":375000,"text":"I was so thrilled to find an interview with the great Russian writer,"},{"time":379000,"text":"Leo Tolstoy, in a New York newspaper in the early 1900s."},{"time":383000,"text":"And in it, Tolstoy told of a trip that he'd recently made"},{"time":386000,"text":"to a very remote area of the Caucasus,"},{"time":388000,"text":"where there were only wild barbarians,"},{"time":390000,"text":"who had never left this part of Russia."},{"time":392000,"text":"Knowing that Tolstoy was in their midst,"},{"time":394000,"text":"they asked him to tell stories of the great men of history."},{"time":397000,"text":"So he said, \"I told them about Napoleon"},{"time":399000,"text":"and Alexander the Great and Frederick the Great"},{"time":401000,"text":"and Julius Caesar, and they loved it."},{"time":403000,"text":"But before I finished, the chief of the barbarians stood up and said,"},{"time":406000,"text":"'But wait, you haven't told us about the greatest ruler of them all."},{"time":409000,"text":"We want to hear about that man who spoke with a voice of thunder,"},{"time":413000,"text":"who laughed like the sunrise,"},{"time":415000,"text":"who came from that place called America, which is so far from here,"},{"time":417000,"text":"that if a young man should travel there,"},{"time":419000,"text":"he would be an old man when he arrived."},{"time":421000,"text":"Tell us of that man. Tell us of Abraham Lincoln.'\""},{"time":425000,"text":"He was stunned."},{"time":426000,"text":"He told them everything he could about Lincoln."},{"time":428000,"text":"And then in the interview he said, \"What made Lincoln so great?"},{"time":430000,"text":"Not as great a general as Napoleon,"},{"time":432000,"text":"not as great a statesman as Frederick the Great.\""},{"time":435000,"text":"But his greatness consisted, and historians would roundly agree,"},{"time":438000,"text":"in the integrity of his character"},{"time":440000,"text":"and the moral fiber of his being."}]},{"cues":[{"time":442000,"text":"So in the end that powerful ambition"},{"time":444000,"text":"that had carried Lincoln through his bleak childhood had been realized."},{"time":447000,"text":"That ambition that had allowed him to laboriously educate himself by himself,"},{"time":452000,"text":"to go through that string of political failures"},{"time":454000,"text":"and the darkest days of the war."},{"time":456000,"text":"His story would be told."},{"time":459000,"text":"So as for that second sphere, not of work, but of love --"},{"time":462000,"text":"encompassing family, friends and colleagues --"},{"time":465000,"text":"it, too, takes work and commitment."},{"time":468000,"text":"The Lyndon Johnson that I saw in the last years of his life,"},{"time":470000,"text":"when I helped him on his memoirs,"},{"time":472000,"text":"was a man who had spent so many years in the pursuit of"},{"time":475000,"text":"work, power and individual success,"},{"time":477000,"text":"that he had absolutely no psychic or emotional resources left"},{"time":481000,"text":"to get him through the days"},{"time":482000,"text":"once the presidency was gone."}]},{"cues":[{"time":485000,"text":"My relationship with him began on a rather curious level."},{"time":488000,"text":"I was selected as a White House Fellow when I was 24 years old."},{"time":491000,"text":"We had a big dance at the White House."},{"time":493000,"text":"President Johnson did dance with me that night."},{"time":495000,"text":"Not that peculiar --"},{"time":496000,"text":"there were only three women out of the 16 White House Fellows."},{"time":498000,"text":"But he did whisper in my ear that he wanted me"},{"time":501000,"text":"to work directly for him in the White House."},{"time":503000,"text":"But it was not to be that simple."},{"time":504000,"text":"For in the months leading up to my selection,"},{"time":506000,"text":"like many young people, I'd been active"},{"time":508000,"text":"in the anti-Vietnam War movement,"},{"time":510000,"text":"and had written an article against Lyndon Johnson,"},{"time":513000,"text":"which unfortunately came out in The New Republic"},{"time":514000,"text":"two days after the dance in the White House."},{"time":516000,"text":"(Laugher)"},{"time":518000,"text":"And the theme of the article was how to remove Lyndon Johnson from power."},{"time":521000,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":522000,"text":"So I was certain he would kick me out of the program."},{"time":525000,"text":"But instead, surprisingly, he said,"},{"time":526000,"text":"\"Oh, bring her down here for a year,"},{"time":528000,"text":"and if I can't win her over, no one can.\""},{"time":531000,"text":"So I did end up working for him in the White House."},{"time":533000,"text":"Eventually accompanied him to his ranch to help him on those memoirs,"},{"time":535000,"text":"never fully understanding why he'd chosen me to spend so many hours with."}]},{"cues":[{"time":539000,"text":"I like to believe it was because I was a good listener."},{"time":542000,"text":"He was a great storyteller."},{"time":543000,"text":"Fabulous, colorful, anecdotal stories."},{"time":545000,"text":"There was a problem with these stories, however,"},{"time":547000,"text":"which I later discovered, which is that half of them weren't true."},{"time":550000,"text":"But they were great, nonetheless."},{"time":551000,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":552000,"text":"So I think that part of his attraction for me was that I loved listening to his tall tales."},{"time":557000,"text":"But I also worried that part of it was that I was then a young woman."},{"time":560000,"text":"And he had somewhat of a minor league womanizing reputation."},{"time":563000,"text":"So I constantly chatted to him about boyfriends,"},{"time":565000,"text":"even when I didn't have any at all."}]},{"cues":[{"time":567000,"text":"Everything was working perfectly,"},{"time":568000,"text":"until one day he said he wanted to discuss our relationship."},{"time":570000,"text":"Sounded very ominous when he took me nearby to the lake,"},{"time":573000,"text":"conveniently called Lake Lyndon Baines Johnson."},{"time":576000,"text":"And there was wine and cheese and a red-checked tablecloth --"},{"time":578000,"text":"all the romantic trappings."},{"time":580000,"text":"And he started out,"},{"time":581000,"text":"\"Doris, more than any other woman I have ever known ... \""},{"time":583000,"text":"And my heart sank."},{"time":585000,"text":"And then he said,"},{"time":586000,"text":"\"You remind me of my mother.\""},{"time":588000,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":589000,"text":"It was pretty embarrassing, given what was going on in my mind."},{"time":595000,"text":"But I must say, the older I've gotten,"},{"time":597000,"text":"the more I realize what an incredible privilege it was"},{"time":599000,"text":"to have spent so many hours with this aging lion of a man."},{"time":602000,"text":"A victor in a thousand contests,"},{"time":604000,"text":"three great civil rights laws, Medicare, aid to education."},{"time":609000,"text":"And yet, roundly defeated in the end by the war in Vietnam."},{"time":612000,"text":"And because he was so sad and so vulnerable,"},{"time":614000,"text":"he opened up to me in ways he never would have"},{"time":616000,"text":"had I known him at the height of his power --"},{"time":618000,"text":"sharing his fears, his sorrows and his worries."},{"time":621000,"text":"And I'd like to believe that the privilege fired within me"},{"time":624000,"text":"the drive to understand the inner person behind the public figure,"},{"time":627000,"text":"that I've tried to bring to each of my books since then."}]},{"cues":[{"time":631000,"text":"But it also brought home to me the lessons"},{"time":633000,"text":"which Erik Erikson had tried to instill in all of us"},{"time":636000,"text":"about the importance of finding balance in life."},{"time":639000,"text":"For on the surface, Lyndon Johnson should have had"},{"time":641000,"text":"everything in the world to feel good about in those last years,"},{"time":645000,"text":"in the sense that he had been elected to the presidency;"},{"time":647000,"text":"he had all the money he needed to pursue"},{"time":649000,"text":"any leisure activity he wanted;"},{"time":651000,"text":"he owned a spacious ranch in the countryside, a penthouse in the city,"},{"time":654000,"text":"sailboats, speedboats."},{"time":656000,"text":"He had servants to answer any whim,"},{"time":658000,"text":"and he had a family who loved him deeply."}]},{"cues":[{"time":662000,"text":"And yet, years of concentration solely on work and individual success"},{"time":665000,"text":"meant that in his retirement he could find no solace"},{"time":669000,"text":"in family, in recreation, in sports or in hobbies."},{"time":673000,"text":"It was almost as if the hole in his heart was so large"},{"time":676000,"text":"that even the love of a family, without work, could not fill it."},{"time":679000,"text":"As his spirits sagged, his body deteriorated"},{"time":682000,"text":"until, I believe, he slowly brought about his own death."},{"time":686000,"text":"In those last years, he said he was so sad"},{"time":688000,"text":"watching the American people look toward a new president and forgetting him."},{"time":692000,"text":"He spoke with immense sadness in his voice,"},{"time":694000,"text":"saying maybe he should have spent more time with his children,"},{"time":696000,"text":"and their children in turn."},{"time":698000,"text":"But it was too late."},{"time":700000,"text":"Despite all that power, all that wealth,"},{"time":702000,"text":"he was alone when he finally died --"},{"time":704000,"text":"his ultimate terror realized."}]},{"cues":[{"time":707000,"text":"So as for that third sphere of play,"},{"time":709000,"text":"which he never had learned to enjoy,"},{"time":711000,"text":"I've learned over the years"},{"time":713000,"text":"that even this sphere requires a commitment of time and energy --"},{"time":716000,"text":"enough so that a hobby, a sport, a love of music,"},{"time":720000,"text":"or art, or literature, or any form of recreation,"},{"time":723000,"text":"can provide true pleasure, relaxation and replenishment."},{"time":727000,"text":"So deep, for instance, was Abraham Lincoln's love of Shakespeare,"},{"time":730000,"text":"that he made time to spend more than a hundred nights in the theater,"},{"time":734000,"text":"even during those dark days of the war."},{"time":736000,"text":"He said, when the lights went down and a Shakespeare play came on,"},{"time":739000,"text":"for a few precious hours he could imagine himself"},{"time":742000,"text":"back in Prince Hal's time."}]},{"cues":[{"time":745000,"text":"But an even more important form of relaxation for him,"},{"time":747000,"text":"that Lyndon Johnson never could enjoy,"},{"time":749000,"text":"was a love of -- somehow -- humor,"},{"time":753000,"text":"and feeling out what hilarious parts of life can produce"},{"time":756000,"text":"as a sidelight to the sadness."},{"time":758000,"text":"He once said that he laughed so he did not cry,"},{"time":762000,"text":"that a good story, for him, was better than a drop of whiskey."},{"time":766000,"text":"His storytelling powers had first been recognized"},{"time":768000,"text":"when he was on the circuit in Illinois."},{"time":769000,"text":"The lawyers and the judges would travel"},{"time":771000,"text":"from one county courthouse to the other,"},{"time":773000,"text":"and when anyone was knowing Lincoln was in town,"},{"time":776000,"text":"they would come from miles around to listen to him tell stories."},{"time":778000,"text":"He would stand with his back against a fire"},{"time":780000,"text":"and entertain the crowd for hours with his winding tales."},{"time":784000,"text":"And all these stories became part of his memory bank,"},{"time":786000,"text":"so he could call on them whenever he needed to."},{"time":789000,"text":"And they're not quite what you might expect from our marble monument."}]},{"cues":[{"time":791000,"text":"One of his favorite stories, for example,"},{"time":793000,"text":"had to do with the Revolutionary War hero, Ethan Allen."},{"time":796000,"text":"And as Lincoln told the story,"},{"time":798000,"text":"Mr. Allen went to Britain after the war."},{"time":800000,"text":"And the British people were still upset"},{"time":802000,"text":"about losing the Revolution,"},{"time":803000,"text":"so they decided to embarrass him a little bit"},{"time":805000,"text":"by putting a huge picture of General Washington"},{"time":808000,"text":"in the only outhouse, where he'd have to encounter it."},{"time":810000,"text":"They figured he'd be upset about the indignity"},{"time":812000,"text":"of George Washington being in an outhouse."},{"time":814000,"text":"But he came out of the outhouse not upset at all."},{"time":816000,"text":"And so they said, \"Well, did you see George Washington in there?\""},{"time":819000,"text":"\"Oh, yes,\" he said, \"perfectly appropriate place for him.\""},{"time":822000,"text":"\"What do you mean?\" they said."},{"time":824000,"text":"\"Well,\" he said, \"there's nothing to make an Englishman shit"},{"time":827000,"text":"faster than the sight of General George Washington.\""},{"time":830000,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":832000,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":834000,"text":"So you can imagine, if you are in the middle of a tense cabinet meeting --"},{"time":838000,"text":"and he had hundreds of these stories --"},{"time":840000,"text":"you would have to relax."},{"time":843000,"text":"So between his nightly treks to the theater,"},{"time":845000,"text":"his story telling, and his extraordinary sense of humor"},{"time":849000,"text":"and his love of quoting Shakespeare and poetry,"},{"time":851000,"text":"he found that form of play which carried him through his days."},{"time":855000,"text":"In my own life, I shall always be grateful"},{"time":858000,"text":"for having found a form of play in my irrational love of baseball."},{"time":861000,"text":"Which allows me, from the beginning of spring training"},{"time":864000,"text":"to the end of the fall,"},{"time":865000,"text":"to have something to occupy my mind and heart"},{"time":867000,"text":"other than my work."}]},{"cues":[{"time":869000,"text":"It all began when I was only six years old,"},{"time":871000,"text":"and my father taught me that mysterious art of keeping score"},{"time":873000,"text":"while listening to baseball games --"},{"time":875000,"text":"so that when he went to work in New York during the day,"},{"time":878000,"text":"I could record for him the history of that afternoon's"},{"time":880000,"text":"Brooklyn Dodgers game."},{"time":882000,"text":"Now, when you're only six years old,"},{"time":883000,"text":"and your father comes home every single night"},{"time":884000,"text":"and listens to you -- as I now realize that I, in excruciating detail,"},{"time":888000,"text":"recounted every single play of every inning"},{"time":889000,"text":"of the game that had just taken place that afternoon."},{"time":892000,"text":"But he made me feel I was telling him a fabulous story."},{"time":895000,"text":"It makes you think there's something magic about history"},{"time":897000,"text":"to keep your father's attention."}]},{"cues":[{"time":899000,"text":"In fact, I'm convinced I learned the narrative art"},{"time":901000,"text":"from those nightly sessions with my father."},{"time":903000,"text":"Because at first, I'd be so excited I would blurt out,"},{"time":905000,"text":"\"The Dodgers won!\" or, \"The Dodgers lost!\""},{"time":907000,"text":"Which took much of the drama of this two-hour telling away."},{"time":910000,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":911000,"text":"So I finally learned you had to tell a story"},{"time":913000,"text":"from beginning to middle to end."},{"time":915000,"text":"I must say, so fervent was my love"},{"time":917000,"text":"of the old Brooklyn Dodgers in those days"},{"time":919000,"text":"that I had to confess in my first confession"},{"time":921000,"text":"two sins that related to baseball."}]},{"cues":[{"time":923000,"text":"The first occurred because the Dodgers' catcher, Roy Campanella,"},{"time":926000,"text":"came to my hometown of Rockville Centre, Long Island,"},{"time":928000,"text":"just as I was in preparation for my first Holy Communion."},{"time":931000,"text":"And I was so excited --"},{"time":933000,"text":"first person I'd ever see outside of Ebbets Field."},{"time":935000,"text":"But it so happened he was speaking in a Protestant Church."},{"time":938000,"text":"When you are brought up as a Catholic, you think"},{"time":939000,"text":"that if you ever set foot in a Protestant Church,"},{"time":941000,"text":"you'll be struck dead at the threshold."},{"time":943000,"text":"So I went to my father in tears, \"What are we going to do?\""},{"time":945000,"text":"He said, \"Don't worry. He's speaking in a parish hall."},{"time":947000,"text":"We're sitting in folding chairs. He's talking about sportsmanship."},{"time":949000,"text":"It's not a sin.\""},{"time":950000,"text":"But as I left that night, I was certain that somehow"},{"time":953000,"text":"I'd traded the life of my everlasting soul"},{"time":955000,"text":"for this one night with Roy Campanella."},{"time":957000,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":958000,"text":"And there were no indulgences around that I could buy."},{"time":961000,"text":"So I had this sin on my soul when I went to my first confession."},{"time":964000,"text":"I told the priest right away."},{"time":965000,"text":"He said, \"No problem. It wasn't a religious service.\""},{"time":967000,"text":"But then, unfortunately, he said, \"And what else, my child?\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":970000,"text":"And then came my second sin."},{"time":972000,"text":"I tried to sandwich it in between talking too much in church,"},{"time":974000,"text":"wishing harm to others, being mean to my sisters."},{"time":977000,"text":"And he said, \"To whom did you wish harm?\""},{"time":979000,"text":"And I had to say that I wished that various New York Yankees players"},{"time":983000,"text":"would break arms, legs and ankles --"},{"time":985000,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":986000,"text":"-- so that the Brooklyn Dodgers could win their first World Series."},{"time":989000,"text":"He said, \"How often do you make these horrible wishes?\""},{"time":990000,"text":"And I had to say, every night when I said my prayers."},{"time":993000,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":994000,"text":"So he said, \"Look, I'll tell you something."},{"time":995000,"text":"I love the Brooklyn Dodgers, as you do,"},{"time":997000,"text":"but I promise you some day they will win fairly and squarely."},{"time":1000000,"text":"You do not need to wish harm on others to make it happen.\""},{"time":1002000,"text":"\"Oh yes,\" I said."},{"time":1003000,"text":"But luckily, my first confession -- to a baseball-loving priest!"},{"time":1006000,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":1007000,"text":"Well, though my father died of a sudden heart attack"},{"time":1010000,"text":"when I was still in my 20s,"},{"time":1011000,"text":"before I had gotten married and had my three sons,"},{"time":1015000,"text":"I have passed his memory -- as well as his love of baseball -- on to my boys."},{"time":1019000,"text":"Though when the Dodgers abandoned us to come to L.A.,"},{"time":1021000,"text":"I lost faith in baseball until I moved to Boston"},{"time":1025000,"text":"and became an irrational Red Socks fan."},{"time":1028000,"text":"And I must say, even now, when I sit with my sons"},{"time":1030000,"text":"with our season tickets,"},{"time":1032000,"text":"I can sometimes close my eyes against the sun"},{"time":1034000,"text":"and imagine myself, a young girl once more, in the presence of my father,"},{"time":1038000,"text":"watching the players of my youth on the grassy fields below:"},{"time":1041000,"text":"Jackie Robinson, Roy Campanella, Pee Wee Reese, and Duke Snider."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1045000,"text":"I must say there is magic in these moments."},{"time":1047000,"text":"When I open my eyes and I see my sons"},{"time":1049000,"text":"in the place where my father once sat,"},{"time":1052000,"text":"I feel an invisible loyalty and love"},{"time":1054000,"text":"linking my sons to the grandfather whose face they never had a chance to see,"},{"time":1058000,"text":"but whose heart and soul they have come to know"},{"time":1060000,"text":"through all the stories I have told."},{"time":1063000,"text":"Which is why, in the end, I shall always be grateful for this curious love of history,"},{"time":1066000,"text":"allowing me to spend a lifetime looking back into the past."},{"time":1070000,"text":"Allowing me to learn from these large figures"},{"time":1073000,"text":"about the struggle for meaning for life."},{"time":1075000,"text":"Allowing me to believe that the private people"},{"time":1077000,"text":"we have loved and lost in our families,"},{"time":1079000,"text":"and the public figures we have respected in our history,"},{"time":1082000,"text":"just as Abraham Lincoln wanted to believe,"},{"time":1084000,"text":"really can live on, so long as we pledge"},{"time":1087000,"text":"to tell and to retell the stories of their lives."},{"time":1091000,"text":"Thank you for letting me be that storyteller today."},{"time":1093000,"text":"(Applause)"},{"time":1094000,"text":"Thank you."}]}]}